WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.440 --> 00:00:01.520
Good morning, family.

00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:10.500
I’m going to talk to you about the time when Jesus woke me up in the middle of the night and ministered to me.

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:20.800
This was around October 2014, and this experience forever changed my life.

00:00:21.093 --> 00:00:33.919
I feel in my heart that when I first started on YouTube, I tried to tell you all what he said, and I thought I would do it again because it gets buried by the algorithm.

00:00:36.022 --> 00:00:38.612
Nobody sees it, especially all the new faces here.

00:00:38.986 --> 00:00:46.427
I want to tell you because this was an experience I had with him that changed my life forever.

00:00:50.035 --> 00:00:54.423
I was sleeping when, all of a sudden, I felt a tap on my right shoulder.

00:00:56.338 --> 00:01:01.867
I was just laying in bed on my side and I heard an audible voice say, 'Wake up.

00:01:01.867 --> 00:01:07.280
' I looked over, and Jesus was standing in my room.

00:01:12.479 --> 00:01:14.280
Most people will ask, 'Was this a vision?

00:01:14.280 --> 00:01:16.439
' No, this was not a vision.

00:01:16.439 --> 00:01:20.409
This was real; he manifested in my house.

00:01:20.613 --> 00:01:25.840
This was one of the only times it was not an open vision.

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:32.853
This was a face-to-face experience with him touching my shoulder and waking me up.

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:39.954
It startled me so much because when you're waking up and rubbing your eyes, you don't recognize things immediately.

00:01:44.879 --> 00:01:46.675
I looked over and saw Jesus standing there.

00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:49.990
I felt his glory and presence and thought, 'Am I dying?

00:01:49.990 --> 00:01:55.420
' My initial reaction was that I was going home and he was coming to get me.

00:01:55.420 --> 00:01:58.539
But he said, 'I've come to answer your prayers.

00:01:58.539 --> 00:02:02.693
' I asked, 'Lord, what's happening?

00:02:02.693 --> 00:02:09.511
' All of a sudden, I looked at my floor, and it was alive.

00:02:09.862 --> 00:02:16.137
The glory of the Lord was so strong in my house that the floor was breathing.

00:02:17.823 --> 00:02:21.100
A portal opened in my floor.

00:02:23.858 --> 00:02:27.424
I flipped my feet over the side of my bed and sat there looking at that portal below my feet.

00:02:33.177 --> 00:02:36.480
Jesus was standing right there at my right hand.

00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:44.090
I was looking at this portal, and it was alive; I could feel the air breathing.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:47.840
It was blowing my hair.

00:02:50.106 --> 00:02:50.533
I could feel the breeze from the portal.

00:03:02.310 --> 00:03:02.540
It was moving like a whirlpool, with light moving down and up like a waterfall.

00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:19.405
My wife was sleeping next to me and never knew any of this happened; she was out cold.

00:03:22.692 --> 00:03:23.146
I said, 'Lord, what do you want me to do?

00:03:23.146 --> 00:03:25.715
' He said, 'I want you to jump inside that portal.

00:03:25.715 --> 00:03:27.290
' I said, 'You want me to jump?

00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:31.268
' He said, 'Brandon, trust me.

00:03:31.268 --> 00:03:36.292
' I looked at him because this was all happening so fast and it was shocking.

00:03:48.788 --> 00:03:49.062
Jesus was standing there in a beautiful white robe, and his hair was flowing because the air from the portal was moving it.

00:04:00.541 --> 00:04:01.769
I said, 'Okay, Lord.

00:04:01.769 --> 00:04:09.404
' All of a sudden, I pushed myself off the edge of the bed and went straight down into that tunnel.

00:04:19.062 --> 00:04:19.348
It was like Mario Brothers on the Nintendo when you go into the tunnel and they transported you to another part.

00:04:19.348 --> 00:04:19.919
That's what it felt like.

00:04:22.171 --> 00:04:26.647
When I jumped inside of that hole, I was taken to the past.

00:04:28.639 --> 00:04:34.754
I was standing at a hospital where my wife and I had our daughter, Megan.

00:04:35.183 --> 00:04:38.460
He said, 'Brandon, I'm giving you a chance.

00:04:38.460 --> 00:04:41.524
You've asked me and asked me to go back in time.

00:04:44.424 --> 00:04:51.600
You always ask, "Lord, if I could just go back in time to when she got her shot and stop that, I could keep her from getting this severe autism.

00:04:51.600 --> 00:05:02.213
"' I’ve always said that I would clean the bathrooms of the church or vacuum the halls if I could just go back in time and warn myself.

00:05:07.999 --> 00:05:15.759
If I could just give myself the opportunity to tell myself not to do that, because it wrecked my life the way it has.

00:05:17.759 --> 00:05:17.1000
I wished I could have a redo.

00:05:17.1000 --> 00:05:23.973
He said, 'I'm going to give you the time to go and change the future.

00:05:24.542 --> 00:05:25.396
I want you to go and tell yourself.

00:05:25.396 --> 00:05:31.377
' I ran up the stairs to the fourth floor of the doctor's office.

00:05:31.377 --> 00:05:38.032
I busted through the doors and saw my younger self sitting there with my daughter and my wife.

00:05:38.032 --> 00:05:41.680
They were getting ready to administer the shot.

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:43.429
I said 'Stop!

00:05:43.429 --> 00:05:45.079
' just like that.

00:05:49.244 --> 00:05:49.529
I froze, and the younger me froze.

00:05:54.263 --> 00:05:56.711
I told the nurse to stop and told my younger self, 'Don't do it.

00:05:56.711 --> 00:06:07.246
' All of a sudden, Jesus came and said, 'I want to show you the power of a choice.

00:06:07.246 --> 00:06:18.466
' He threw his hand open and put a screen up in front of my face.

00:06:18.466 --> 00:06:25.520
Everything froze in time, and he showed me a future where Megan didn't get that shot.

00:06:31.128 --> 00:06:31.430
He painted it all out in front of me for each year.

00:06:40.861 --> 00:06:41.083
He said, 'Brandon, I want to show you what happened by this choice.

00:06:41.083 --> 00:06:56.160
' I told him, 'Lord, you've called me to be a healing evangelist, but I can't pray for people because I'll look like a hypocrite while my own daughter is still overcome.

00:06:56.160 --> 00:07:04.440
I've laid hands on her probably a thousand times and never felt the anointing go into her.

00:07:04.440 --> 00:07:06.880
' I’ve always kept this private.

00:07:11.109 --> 00:07:11.291
I wouldn't even let anyone say the word 'autistic.

00:07:11.291 --> 00:07:18.360
' I would want to fight you if you did because faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:07:18.360 --> 00:07:31.173
I didn't even let the doctors diagnose her at first because I was so upset; I didn't want them speaking those words because life and death are in the power of the tongue.

00:07:37.379 --> 00:07:37.988
I got really flaky about it because I was scared of the diagnosis and didn't want anyone speaking anything over my child.

00:07:37.988 --> 00:07:40.148
I'm telling you all, it was bondage.

00:07:40.148 --> 00:07:47.111
And she would rock in the corner and scream at night all night long after it happened.

00:07:47.111 --> 00:08:00.940
I'm telling you, it was literal hell on earth for years before I would allow them to diagnose her and for her to get help through therapies and stuff, because I was believing God by faith because I'm the big healing evangelist and because of all these prophecies that were given over my life.

00:08:06.399 --> 00:08:06.559
So here I am.

00:08:20.806 --> 00:08:21.400
The Lord threw all this out in front of me and he said, "Brandon, I want to show you what happens with Megan.

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:25.291
" Now, Megan is developing normally, but you're not changing.

00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:29.040
The pressure from her circumstance changes you.

00:08:31.211 --> 00:08:31.485
It puts you through the refiner's fire.

00:08:31.759 --> 00:08:34.600
And he told me, "Brandon, I did not do this.

00:08:35.710 --> 00:08:42.685
I did not cause her to be autistic, but whatever the devil meant for bad, I will turn it for good in your favor.

00:08:53.769 --> 00:08:54.053
And no matter how bad the circumstance is, I will always turn it for good in your favor.

00:08:54.053 --> 00:08:56.811
Whatever the devil meant for bad for you.

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:07.208
" But he said, "I'm not the one that caused the autism.

00:09:07.208 --> 00:09:11.466
It's a fallen world.

00:09:11.466 --> 00:09:13.246
Things happen.

00:09:13.246 --> 00:09:17.253
You know what I'm saying?

00:09:17.253 --> 00:09:21.860
" That's the way he painted the picture to me.

00:09:28.320 --> 00:09:35.051
I want to say exactly what he said, but it's been so long that I'm forgetting some of the words, so you have to just bear with me here.

00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:41.960
I'm painting the picture of how Jesus told me.

00:09:54.440 --> 00:09:54.640
So he painted the picture in front of me and I went from year to year.

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:03.320
He said, "Brandon, do you see right here?

00:10:08.308 --> 00:10:14.800
You have a lot of anger issues that you're still overcoming.

00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:18.507
" And he said, "You were very verbally abusive to your wife," which I was.

00:10:18.507 --> 00:10:21.430
I belittled her a lot when I first got married.

00:10:21.430 --> 00:10:25.737
I was young and stupid and I didn't handle myself like I should.

00:10:25.737 --> 00:10:37.033
And he said, because of this right here, it develops a wall between you and your wife over the course of time.

00:10:37.519 --> 00:10:55.035
Megan's developing normally, but he said your wife leaves you right here—and he pointed out the year, which is nobody's business—but he told me, "She is going to leave you right here and she takes your daughter and they move to Texas.

00:10:55.035 --> 00:11:00.331
" And he said, "And you see her every two weeks on the weekends.

00:11:00.331 --> 00:11:05.325
You don't have full custody because she moves and lives with her mom.

00:11:05.811 --> 00:11:10.690
Whenever this takes place, you see her on the weekends.

00:11:10.690 --> 00:11:16.605
" And he said, Diana gets remarried to another man.

00:11:16.605 --> 00:11:21.977
And he showed me the man and said, "This is when your wife gets remarried.

00:11:21.977 --> 00:11:29.097
" And he said, "Then you become very bitter and angry because of the choices that you've made.

00:11:29.097 --> 00:11:36.971
You're off track with your call and what I've called you to do because this is what's changing you.

00:11:39.629 --> 00:11:45.360
All this pressure from having a child with special needs is molding your character.

00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:46.800
It's breaking you down.

00:11:46.800 --> 00:11:50.462
It's making you pliable in my hands.

00:11:50.462 --> 00:11:56.411
Yes, the pressure—I did not do it, but I will use it.

00:11:58.631 --> 00:12:01.160
" Does that make sense?

00:12:01.160 --> 00:12:17.160
So I saw the pressure of my daughter every single year without having the pressure from this because she didn't have the autism anymore; she became normal and she became an adult.

00:12:26.245 --> 00:12:29.360
And he said, "Brandon, your son was never born.

00:12:29.360 --> 00:12:40.880
Your son that your wife has right now was never born, and your daughter that will be born in the future will not be born.

00:12:49.920 --> 00:12:50.827
And there is a call on her life for the thousand years for things that I'm going to do with a thousand years.

00:12:50.827 --> 00:13:01.620
There are things that are set in motion that will not be put in motion because of choices.

00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:15.370
" He said, "You say that you've messed up your life and you can't be used now because of Megan.

00:13:15.370 --> 00:13:26.462
" But he said, "Brandon, all things work together for good for those that love the Lord and are heirs and are called according to his purpose.

00:13:26.462 --> 00:13:29.209
You're not big enough to mess up your life.

00:13:29.209 --> 00:13:34.305
You're not big enough to derail your life.

00:13:50.979 --> 00:13:54.195
" He said, "If you are in right standing with me and you keep yourself in right standing and seek me daily, building your relationship with me, I will take what the devil meant for bad and turn it for good in your favor.

00:13:54.195 --> 00:14:00.409
There's not enough power in hell to derail the call on your life, son.

00:14:00.409 --> 00:14:10.639
Even with how bad you feel you've messed up with this, I'll turn it around for good in your favor if you keep seeking me.

00:14:10.639 --> 00:14:14.279
" So I want to tell you this.

00:14:28.688 --> 00:14:29.120
Whenever he told me this, I saw each year play out before my face, up until that point.

00:14:29.120 --> 00:14:33.759
My son wasn't born; my youngest daughter wasn't born.

00:14:33.759 --> 00:14:44.876
All these bad decisions that I had made and the pressure I had from having a child with special needs had molded me to what I am today.

00:14:44.876 --> 00:14:56.154
And God took what the devil meant for bad and he turned it around for good in my favor because it molded me and created a better person out of me.

00:14:56.154 --> 00:15:13.189
If you've never been a caretaker of somebody with special needs whenever they're messing themselves or having their cycle or going through the hell that I went through in the beginning, the tears that I cried...

00:15:13.189 --> 00:15:15.892
she only slept two hours a night.

00:15:15.892 --> 00:15:16.817
It was awful.

00:15:18.239 --> 00:15:18.479
And that lasted for years.

00:15:18.479 --> 00:15:22.987
I would go to work and I would be so tired.

00:15:22.987 --> 00:15:35.902
I'd fall asleep laying against the wall and I'd catch myself because I was so tired cleaning toilets, and I was barely making any money at all, living on food stamps for years.

00:15:35.902 --> 00:15:40.560
I'm doing this and my wife is at home crying and I can't wait to get home.

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:45.218
I can't deal with this anymore because Megan was so bad.

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:49.771
And she'd say, "Can you come and relieve me and just get the car?

00:15:49.771 --> 00:15:54.857
" because we only had one car, "and drive her around just so she'll fall asleep while you're driving around.

00:15:54.857 --> 00:16:07.982
" Because we couldn't even get her to fall asleep in the house because even clothes—she didn't wear clothes for years because the touch of the clothing on her skin weirded her out and she'd have to take her clothes off.

00:16:07.982 --> 00:16:11.550
Everybody was thinking, "Well, this kid's just wearing a diaper.

00:16:11.550 --> 00:16:29.394
" We got her to where she'd wear a diaper in public because she didn't even want to have a diaper on, and so she'd try to be nude because she didn't want the texture of the diaper on.

00:16:29.394 --> 00:16:38.933
So we had to get her to the point where she would just wear a diaper, and we were ecstatic about that.

00:16:38.933 --> 00:16:46.720
Then we were ecstatic just to get a t-shirt on her, or one of those big princess dresses.

00:16:46.720 --> 00:16:55.279
We tried to put one of those nightgowns on her, so she would walk around with a nightgown on.

00:17:08.283 --> 00:17:08.595
It took us another year or so before we got her there.

00:17:10.659 --> 00:17:13.714
And it was like all this time was pressure, pressure, pressure.

00:17:13.714 --> 00:17:15.199
And it molds you.

00:17:15.199 --> 00:17:20.950
And what happens with the diamond whenever that coal is under pressure?

00:17:20.950 --> 00:17:23.134
It transforms into something so beautiful.

00:17:35.453 --> 00:17:35.707
But without the pressure, it would never transform into what it was supposed to be.

00:17:35.707 --> 00:17:38.663
Just like it is with a caterpillar.

00:17:40.773 --> 00:17:43.025
You have a beautiful caterpillar in a cocoon.

00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:57.460
And if you remove that cocoon before it's time and they don't have the strength—the monarch butterfly has the strength to push against that cocoon—it will never develop the strength to fly.

00:17:58.569 --> 00:18:03.257
The pressure of the cocoon makes that caterpillar that turns into a butterfly into who it is.

00:18:07.949 --> 00:18:14.280
And without that pressure on its life, it will never be what it's supposed to be because we think, "Well, we'll just remove that off of there.

00:18:28.274 --> 00:18:29.700
" But if you remove that pressure of him trying to fight to get out of that, that caterpillar wouldn't be a beautiful monarch butterfly.

00:18:29.700 --> 00:18:34.703
So, a lot of times I see what people go through.

00:18:34.703 --> 00:18:42.560
They think that the storms of life are destroying them, but yet they're making them into who they are.

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:47.778
The pressure of life develops you into something great.

00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:55.450
We think, 'God, can you remove this or that?

00:18:55.450 --> 00:19:02.320
' But He tells you today, 'All things are possible to him that believes.

00:19:02.320 --> 00:19:08.520
' And not only that, 'Son, I'm going to turn it around for good.

00:19:08.520 --> 00:19:12.980
What the devil meant for bad, I'm going to turn for good in your favor.

00:19:12.980 --> 00:19:15.860
' That's what He's trying to tell you all.

00:19:15.860 --> 00:19:19.006
Don't always embrace it; fight and resist it.

00:19:19.006 --> 00:19:25.330
Just like that caterpillar is up there fighting and that butterfly is going, 'I want out of this!

00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:26.799
I want out of this!

00:19:26.799 --> 00:19:28.830
' Fight spiritually against it.

00:19:28.830 --> 00:19:31.049
Don't embrace it and coddle it.

00:19:31.049 --> 00:19:31.920
Resist it.

00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:33.977
Submit yourself therefore unto God.

00:19:33.977 --> 00:19:36.986
Resist the devil and he will flee.

00:19:36.986 --> 00:19:43.250
But when trials and things happen, we fight against them and we won't let them stay.

00:19:43.250 --> 00:19:47.086
But the process of the fight is what changes us.

00:19:53.849 --> 00:19:54.187
A lot of times it's the word; it's staying the course.

00:19:57.588 --> 00:19:59.142
And in this situation, like I said, God did not do this.

00:20:01.235 --> 00:20:02.551
The devil comes to kill, steal, and destroy.

00:20:02.551 --> 00:20:07.227
But the Bible says that He has come that we might have life, and life more abundantly.

00:20:07.227 --> 00:20:14.880
But in this situation, it's what I needed obviously to develop who I was a little bit more.

00:20:24.480 --> 00:20:24.720
And whenever it was all over, He preached me a sermon.

00:20:25.360 --> 00:20:32.462
He encouraged me and told me there was a call on my life.

00:20:32.462 --> 00:20:37.787
He told me that He was going to use me for ministry.

00:20:37.787 --> 00:20:59.359
He told me that this pressure that I was going through at the time would subside, that the storms of life would not always be there with the intensity of what it was then, but that we would always go from glory to glory to glory and we mature and we are able to handle that pressure a little better.

00:20:59.359 --> 00:21:02.089
There's more pressure now than I've ever had before.

00:21:02.089 --> 00:21:03.404
But it's different.

00:21:03.404 --> 00:21:14.418
It's different because we're going from glory to glory, and that potter is putting His hand on that clay and He's molding us.

00:21:14.418 --> 00:21:22.526
We have this treasure in earthen vessels that the excellency of the power will be known of Him and not of us.

00:21:32.540 --> 00:21:32.760
And if you think, 'Well, I've derailed my life.

00:21:38.411 --> 00:21:38.594
I was a bad person.

00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:41.360
I murdered, I raped, I robbed.

00:21:43.485 --> 00:21:47.133
I did whatever, and God can't use me now,' or 'I was the victim of that,'—that's what I'm trying to say.

00:21:47.133 --> 00:21:49.751
You say, 'I was the victim of a rape.

00:21:51.679 --> 00:21:52.346
I was a victim of an abusive husband.

00:21:55.049 --> 00:21:56.596
I was a victim of a sexually abusive father, or all these things, and I'm disqualified.

00:21:59.840 --> 00:22:00.098
God can't use me.

00:22:01.901 --> 00:22:02.159
I'm broken.

00:22:02.159 --> 00:22:09.171
' What the devil meant for bad to destroy you, God will turn it around in your favor.

00:22:09.171 --> 00:22:16.200
What was meant to try to derail and destroy you, He will take and turn into beauty from ashes.

00:22:17.660 --> 00:22:31.400
And I'm telling you, don't give up on what you are believing for because those circumstances and that pain are what's going to help you to help somebody else that's walked through the pain and is walking through it right now.

00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:38.224
You'll be able to minister to somebody and have compassion on them when somebody else won't.

00:22:38.224 --> 00:22:45.480
Like somebody who's been diagnosed with something really bad and you were diagnosed with it and God healed you.

00:22:52.089 --> 00:22:52.320
You have more compassion for that person, like I have for children with special needs.

00:22:52.320 --> 00:23:09.408
When I see a child with special needs in the store or whatever, my spirit literally weeps for them with the compassion that I have towards families that are going through this and I pray for them.

00:23:09.408 --> 00:23:22.264
I'm telling you, I have more compassion to pray for them than I have probably for anybody else because I've been through the pain.

00:23:41.822 --> 00:23:51.006
And when you walk through the pain of something, you're able to help somebody else that's going through it because you've been there.

00:23:51.006 --> 00:23:53.387
You've cried those tears.

00:23:53.387 --> 00:24:02.224
You've held your head up through the storm and you can say to them, 'Hey, you can make it, too.

00:24:02.224 --> 00:24:08.720
' And you may be going through the storm and thinking, 'Man, I don't know how I'm going to get through this.

00:24:09.467 --> 00:24:12.780
I don't know how I'm going to breathe another minute.

00:24:12.780 --> 00:24:17.490
' There were days I wanted to drive my car off the side of a bridge.

00:24:29.240 --> 00:24:29.700
I didn't care if I got hit by a train.

00:24:48.925 --> 00:24:49.360
That's how much pain I was going through on the way to work or on the way home because I knew what I was facing when I got there.

00:24:49.360 --> 00:24:56.640
But I fought through it because I knew that God had a plan for my life.

00:24:56.640 --> 00:25:05.634
But I'm talking about the darkest, darkest bottom of the pit, and you're thinking, 'I don't think I'm going to make this.

00:25:05.634 --> 00:25:09.679
' There were days that were that dark.

00:25:17.050 --> 00:25:17.320
I'm just being real with y'all.

00:25:26.205 --> 00:25:26.468
You may not want to hear that, but it's real.

00:25:26.468 --> 00:25:27.520
This is raw.

00:25:27.520 --> 00:25:30.825
It's real, and you need to hear it.

00:25:30.825 --> 00:25:45.920
There were days that I thought, while cleaning, and you didn't have enough money to buy a gallon of milk, and you're thinking, 'God, I don't know how I'm going to make it.

00:25:45.920 --> 00:25:51.720
' Those days when you're crying yourself to sleep and nobody around you cares.

00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:54.542
Nobody around you is praying for you.

00:25:54.542 --> 00:25:56.959
You felt like you're all alone.

